    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "First Space Walk\nMarch 19, 1965 • Moscow, U.S.S.R.\nCCCP\n6к\n• ПОЧТА\nЛЕТЧИК-КОСМОНАВТ СССР С С С Р\n18-19. . 1965 г.\n19038415\n(5) СССР",
      "International Tributes to the History of Flight\nFirst Space Walk\nThe launch of the 12,529-Ib. Voskhod 2 spacecraft\nThe full-color cachet pictures Aleksei Leonov dur-\ncarrying cosmonauts Pavel Belyayev and Aleksei Leo-\ning his space \"walk.\" He is linked to the Voskhod\nnov was uneventful. However, it was the flight plan\n2 spacecraft via a tether measuring more than 20\nthat had Russian officials on edge. It called for Leonov\nfeet long. Behind him is a spectacular view of the\nto exit the craft and make the first space \"walk.\"\nearth.\nAs Voskhod 2 orbited the earth at speeds exceed-\nMint Stamp: The mint stamp on this Cover was issued\ning 17,000 miles per hour, Leonov attached the \"um-\nby Russia in 1965 to call attention to the achievement\nbilical cord\"' that would link him to the craft and\nof the Voskhod 2 flight. It features a portrait of cos-\nsupply voice communications as well as life-sustain-\nmonaut Aleksei Leonov, a lieutenant colonel in the\ning oxygen. He then passed through the airlock and\nRussian air force.\nentered the vast vacuum of space. Because he car-\nried no self-propulsion device, Leonov floated freely\nPostmark: This Cover was postmarked in the Russian\nfor the full ten-minute duration of his outer space\ncapital city of Moscow on March 19, 1984, the anni-\nadventure.\nversary of the first space walk.\n© Postal Commemorative Society\nPion: 0560.043"
